    'bsp-op-sdp-software-removal': {
        title: 'Software Removal Sync – Browser Security Plus → ServiceDesk Plus',
        content: `
            <h3>Description</h3>
            <p>When <strong>commercial software</strong> is removed or uninstalled from Browser Security Plus's software catalog, this feature automatically updates the corresponding software record in <strong>ServiceDesk Plus</strong>. This keeps the asset management software inventory accurate.</p>

            <h3>How This Works</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>An administrator removes a commercial software entry from Browser Security Plus's software inventory or catalog.</li>
                <li>Browser Security Plus sends a removal notification to ServiceDesk Plus via the integration API.</li>
                <li>ServiceDesk Plus updates or removes the corresponding software record from its asset database.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Integration between Browser Security Plus and ServiceDesk Plus must be active.</li>
                <li>The software must have been previously synced to ServiceDesk Plus.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Known Limitations</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Only commercial software tracked in Browser Security Plus's inventory is affected.</li>
                <li>Freeware or untracked software removals are not synced.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Logs for Troubleshooting</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Browser Security Plus server:</strong> <code>&lt;Install_Dir&gt;/logs/sdpintegration.txt</code></li>
            </ul>
            
        `,
        links: []
    },
    'bsp-op-sdp-trayicon': {
        title: 'Trayicon Requests as ServiceDesk Plus Tickets',
        content: `
            <h3>Description</h3>
            <p>When an end user right-clicks the <strong>Browser Security Plus agent tray icon</strong> on their desktop and submits a request (e.g., software installation, hardware issue), a ticket is automatically created in <strong>ServiceDesk Plus</strong>. This bridges the gap between the endpoint agent and the helpdesk, ensuring end-user requests are captured without manual intervention.</p>

            <h3>How This Works</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>The end user clicks the Browser Security Plus tray icon in the system tray and selects <strong>"Raise a Request"</strong>.</li>
                <li>They fill in details like subject, description, and priority.</li>
                <li>The request is sent to the Browser Security Plus server, which forwards it to ServiceDesk Plus via API.</li>
                <li>A new ticket is created in ServiceDesk Plus with the user's details, machine information, and request description pre-populated.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>The Browser Security Plus agent must be installed on the endpoint with the tray icon enabled.</li>
                <li>Integration between Browser Security Plus and ServiceDesk Plus must be configured under Admin → Integrations.</li>
                <li>The "Trayicon requests" feature must be enabled in the integration settings.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Known Limitations</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>The tray icon must be visible and enabled on the endpoint (it can be hidden via policy).</li>
                <li>If the agent cannot reach the Browser Security Plus server, requests will be queued locally and sent when connectivity is restored.</li>
                <li>Attachment support depends on the configured maximum file size.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Logs for Troubleshooting</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Agent side:</strong> <code>&lt;Agent_Dir&gt;/logs/selfserviceportal.log</code></li>
                <li><strong>Browser Security Plus server:</strong> <code>&lt;Install_Dir&gt;/logs/sdpintegration.txt</code></li>
                <li>Verify the tray icon is visible on the endpoint (check agent settings or group policy).</li>
            </ul>
            
        `,
        links: []
    },
    'bsp-op-snow-basic-asset-post': {
        title: 'Asset Data Post to ServiceNow – Browser Security Plus',
        content: `
            <h3>Description</h3>
            <p>This feature posts <strong>asset inventory data</strong> (hardware and software) from <strong>Browser Security Plus</strong> to <strong>ServiceNow's CMDB</strong>. It keeps the ServiceNow asset database accurate and current by syncing data discovered by the Browser Security Plus agent.</p>

            <h3>How This Works</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Configure the ServiceNow integration in Browser Security Plus under Admin → Integrations → ServiceNow.</li>
                <li>Provide ServiceNow instance URL, credentials (or OAuth), and select the data types to sync.</li>
                <li>Browser Security Plus pushes asset data (computer name, OS, hardware specs, installed software) to ServiceNow via REST API.</li>
                <li>Assets are matched in ServiceNow using serial number or computer name to prevent duplicates.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>ServiceNow instance with CMDB and REST API access.</li>
                <li>A ServiceNow service account with CMDB write permissions.</li>
                <li>Browser Security Plus must have outbound HTTPS access to the ServiceNow instance.</li>
                <li>Install the ManageEngine app from the ServiceNow Store if required.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Known Limitations</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Custom CMDB fields in ServiceNow may not be automatically populated — field mapping may require configuration.</li>
                <li>Sync is one-directional (from Browser Security Plus to ServiceNow).</li>
                <li>Rate limiting on ServiceNow REST API may slow bulk asset syncs.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Logs for Troubleshooting</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Browser Security Plus server:</strong> <code>&lt;Install_Dir&gt;/logs/snowintegration.log</code></li>
                <li>Verify ServiceNow instance URL and credentials under integration settings.</li>
                <li>Check ServiceNow's System Logs → REST API for errors.</li>
            </ul>
            
        `,
        links: []
    },
    'bsp-op-snow-basic-asset-removal': {
        title: 'Asset Removal Sync to ServiceNow – Browser Security Plus',
        content: `
            <h3>Description</h3>
            <p>When a device is removed from the <strong>Scope of Management (SoM)</strong> in <strong>Browser Security Plus</strong>, this feature updates or removes the corresponding <strong>Configuration Item (CI)</strong> in <strong>ServiceNow's CMDB</strong>. This keeps the CMDB clean by removing stale entries for decommissioned devices.</p>

            <h3>How This Works</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>A device is removed from Browser Security Plus's Scope of Management (via uninstall, decommission, etc.).</li>
                <li>Browser Security Plus sends a removal notification to ServiceNow via REST API.</li>
                <li>Based on configuration, the CI in ServiceNow is either deleted, retired, or marked as decommissioned.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>ServiceNow integration must be configured and active in Browser Security Plus.</li>
                <li>The asset must have been previously synced to ServiceNow.</li>
                <li>The ServiceNow service account must have CI write/delete permissions.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Known Limitations</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>If the integration is down at removal time, the action will not be retroactively sent.</li>
                <li>Bulk removals may be rate-limited by ServiceNow's API.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Logs for Troubleshooting</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Browser Security Plus server:</strong> <code>&lt;Install_Dir&gt;/logs/snowintegration.log</code></li>
                <li>Search for "removal" or "delete" in the integration log.</li>
            </ul>
            
        `,
        links: []
    },
