    'bsp-op-snow-basic-op-owner-assign': {
        title: 'Auto-Assign Last Logged-In User as Asset Owner',
        content: `
            <h3>Description</h3>
            <p>This feature automatically maps the <strong>last logged-in user</strong> detected by the Browser Security Plus agent to the corresponding asset in <strong>ServiceNow</strong>, setting them as the asset owner. This helps keep the asset-owner mapping current without manual updates.</p>

            <h3>How This Works</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>The Browser Security Plus agent detects the currently logged-in user on the endpoint during each scan.</li>
                <li>When the inventory data is synced to ServiceNow, the "last logged-in user" field is included.</li>
                <li>If Auto-Assign is enabled, ServiceNow automatically updates the asset owner to match this user.</li>
                <li>If the user is not found in ServiceNow's user directory, the mapping may be skipped or a new user record may be created (depending on configuration).</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Inventory asset sync between Browser Security Plus and ServiceNow must be active.</li>
                <li>The "Auto-assign users" option must be enabled in the integration feature settings.</li>
                <li>User records should exist in ServiceNow for the mapping to work correctly.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Known Limitations</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Only the <strong>last logged-in user</strong> is assigned — shared or multi-user machines may have frequently changing owners.</li>
                <li>Service accounts or system accounts that log in may be incorrectly mapped if not filtered out.</li>
                <li>The user must exist in ServiceNow's user database for the assignment to succeed.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Logs for Troubleshooting</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Browser Security Plus server:</strong> <code>&lt;Install_Dir&gt;/logs/sdpintegration.txt</code></li>
                <li>Search for "auto-assign" or "owner" in the integration log.</li>
                <li>Verify the user record exists in ServiceNow under User Management.</li>
            </ul>
            
        `,
        links: []
    },
