    'dcp-op-syslog-cloud-audit-logs': {
        title: 'Audit Log Sync to Syslog/SIEM – Device Control Plus',
        content: `
            <h3>Description</h3>
            <p>This feature exports <strong>Action Log Viewer data (audit logs)</strong> from <strong>Device Control Plus</strong> to a <strong>Syslog server or SIEM</strong> solution. This allows the security operations team to correlate endpoint management events with other security data sources in a centralized SIEM.</p>

            <h3>How This Works</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Enable the Syslog integration in Device Control Plus under Admin → Integrations → Syslog/SIEM.</li>
                <li>Configure the Syslog server IP/hostname, port, and protocol (UDP/TCP/TLS).</li>
                <li>Device Control Plus sends audit log entries in syslog-compatible format (RFC 5424 or CEF) to the configured server.</li>
                <li>The SIEM/Syslog server ingests the data for correlation, alerting, and compliance reporting.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>A Syslog server or SIEM solution (e.g., EventLog Analyzer, Splunk, QRadar, ArcSight) that accepts syslog input.</li>
                <li>Network connectivity from Device Control Plus server to the Syslog server on the configured port.</li>
                <li>The integration must be enabled in Device Control Plus.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Known Limitations</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>UDP-based syslog does not guarantee delivery — use TCP/TLS for reliable transmission.</li>
                <li>Only audit log data is forwarded. Patch/vulnerability data requires separate integrations.</li>
                <li>Firewall rules must allow outbound traffic from Device Control Plus to the Syslog server.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Logs for Troubleshooting</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Device Control Plus server:</strong> <code>&lt;Install_Dir&gt;/logs/syslogintegration.log</code></li>
                <li>Verify syslog server IP, port, and protocol in Device Control Plus → Admin → Integrations.</li>
                <li>Test connectivity: <code>telnet &lt;syslog_server_ip&gt; &lt;port&gt;</code> from the Device Control Plus server.</li>
            </ul>
            
        `,
        links: []
    },
