    'mdm-op-splunk-audit-logs': {
        title: 'Audit Log Sync to Splunk – Mobile Device Manager Plus',
        content: `
            <h3>Description</h3>
            <p>This feature sends <strong>Action Log Viewer (audit log)</strong> data from <strong>Mobile Device Manager Plus</strong> to <strong>Splunk</strong>. Security teams can use Splunk's correlation and alerting to monitor administrative actions, configuration changes, and user activities captured by Mobile Device Manager Plus.</p>

            <h3>How This Works</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Enable the Splunk integration in Mobile Device Manager Plus under Admin → Integrations → Splunk.</li>
                <li>Configure the Splunk HTTP Event Collector (HEC) endpoint URL and token.</li>
                <li>Mobile Device Manager Plus periodically forwards audit log entries to Splunk's HEC endpoint via HTTPS.</li>
                <li>In Splunk, the data is indexed and available for search, dashboards, and alerting.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Splunk instance with HTTP Event Collector (HEC) enabled.</li>
                <li>A valid HEC token configured in Splunk.</li>
                <li>Mobile Device Manager Plus server must have outbound HTTPS access to the Splunk HEC URL.</li>
                <li>The integration must be enabled in Mobile Device Manager Plus's admin settings.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Known Limitations</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Only action log viewer data (audit logs) is synced — operational data like inventory or patch status requires separate configuration.</li>
                <li>If the Splunk HEC endpoint is unreachable, logs may be queued and sent once connectivity is restored (depends on retry configuration).</li>
                <li>Large environments with high audit log volume may require Splunk indexing capacity planning.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Logs for Troubleshooting</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Mobile Device Manager Plus server:</strong> <code>&lt;Install_Dir&gt;/logs/splunkintegration.log</code></li>
                <li>Verify HEC token and URL in Mobile Device Manager Plus → Admin → Integrations → Splunk.</li>
                <li>In Splunk, search <code>index=* sourcetype="mobile_device_manager_plus"</code> to verify data receipt.</li>
            </ul>
            
        `,
        links: []
    },
