    'pmp-jira-asset-data': {
        title: 'Asset Data Sync to Jira – Patch Manager Plus',
        content: `
            <h3>Description</h3>
            <p>This feature makes <strong>asset inventory data</strong> from <strong>Patch Manager Plus</strong> available within <strong>Jira</strong>, allowing support teams to see device details (hardware, software, user) directly within Jira issues.</p>

            <h3>How This Works</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Install the ManageEngine Jira plugin/app from the Atlassian Marketplace.</li>
                <li>Configure the Patch Manager Plus server URL and API key in the Jira plugin settings.</li>
                <li>When viewing a Jira issue linked to a managed asset, the plugin fetches and displays asset details from Patch Manager Plus.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>ManageEngine Jira integration plugin installed in Jira.</li>
                <li>API key configured in Patch Manager Plus for the Jira integration.</li>
                <li>Network access from Jira server to Patch Manager Plus server.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Known Limitations</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Asset data is fetched on-demand (not pre-synced) — response time depends on network latency.</li>
                <li>Only assets managed by Patch Manager Plus are available.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Logs for Troubleshooting</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Patch Manager Plus server:</strong> <code>&lt;Install_Dir&gt;/logs/jiraintegration.log</code></li>
                <li>Check Jira plugin settings for connectivity errors.</li>
            </ul>
            
        `,
        links: []
    },
    'pmp-jira-iframe': {
        title: 'Load Patch Manager Plus iFrame in Jira',
        content: `
            <h3>Description</h3>
            <p>This feature embeds the full <strong>Patch Manager Plus</strong> web console inside <strong>Jira</strong> as an iFrame. Technicians can access Patch Manager Plus features without leaving the Jira interface, reducing context-switching and improving productivity.</p>

            <h3>How This Works</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Once the integration is configured, the Patch Manager Plus module appears as a tab or section within the Jira console.</li>
                <li>Clicking the tab loads the Patch Manager Plus web interface inside an iFrame within the Jira page.</li>
                <li>Technicians can navigate Patch Manager Plus features, view reports, and perform actions — all within the Jira browser session.</li>
                <li>Authentication is handled via the integration's API key/token, so separate login is not required.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Both Patch Manager Plus and Jira servers must be reachable from the technician's browser.</li>
                <li>Integration must be configured with valid API credentials.</li>
                <li>If using HTTPS, both products must have valid SSL certificates. Mixed content (HTTP inside HTTPS) will be blocked by browsers.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Known Limitations</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>If the Patch Manager Plus server has <code>X-Frame-Options</code> set to DENY or SAMEORIGIN, the iFrame will not load. This header may need to be adjusted.</li>
                <li>Browser security policies may block cross-origin iFrames if the domains differ significantly.</li>
                <li>Performance may be slightly slower than directly accessing the Patch Manager Plus console, as the page is loaded within another page.</li>
                <li>Some browser extensions (ad blockers, privacy tools) may interfere with iFrame loading.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Logs for Troubleshooting</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Check the <strong>browser developer console</strong> (F12 → Console tab) for Content Security Policy (CSP) or X-Frame-Options errors.</li>
                <li><strong>Patch Manager Plus server:</strong> <code>&lt;Install_Dir&gt;/logs/serverout.txt</code> for access/authentication errors.</li>
                <li>Ensure both servers use the same protocol (both HTTP or both HTTPS).</li>
            </ul>
            
        `,
        links: []
    },
