    'vmp-op-jira-op-remote-control': {
        title: 'Remote Control from Jira Tickets',
        content: `
            <h3>Description</h3>
            <p>This feature allows technicians to launch a remote desktop connection to any managed endpoint directly from within <strong>Jira</strong>. Instead of switching between consoles, technicians can resolve issues faster by accessing the machine while viewing the ticket.</p>

            <h3>How This Works</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>When a technician opens a ticket in Jira that has an associated asset managed by Vulnerability Manager Plus, a <strong>"Remote Control"</strong> action button appears.</li>
                <li>Clicking the button sends a request to the Vulnerability Manager Plus server via API, which initiates a remote session to the endpoint's agent.</li>
                <li>The remote viewer opens in a new browser tab or the native remote tool, providing full desktop access.</li>
                <li>Session details (start time, duration, technician) are logged for audit purposes.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>The Vulnerability Manager Plus agent must be installed and online on the target machine.</li>
                <li>Vulnerability Manager Plus and Jira integration must be configured and active.</li>
                <li>The technician must have remote control permissions in Vulnerability Manager Plus.</li>
                <li>Ports required for remote control (typically 8020, 8443) must be open between the technician's browser and the Vulnerability Manager Plus server.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Known Limitations</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Only computers that have the Vulnerability Manager Plus agent installed and reporting will be available for remote control.</li>
                <li>If the endpoint is offline or unreachable, the remote session cannot be established.</li>
                <li>Pop-up blockers may prevent the remote viewer from launching in a new tab.</li>
                <li>Some VPN configurations may block the required ports.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Logs for Troubleshooting</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Vulnerability Manager Plus server:</strong> <code>&lt;Install_Dir&gt;/logs/remotecontrol.log</code></li>
                <li><strong>Agent side:</strong> <code>&lt;Agent_Dir&gt;/logs/rcgateway.log</code></li>
                <li>Check browser console for pop-up blocker errors.</li>
                <li>Verify the agent is online under Vulnerability Manager Plus → Scope of Management.</li>
            </ul>
            
        `,
        links: []
    },
    'vmp-op-jira-op-tools-action': {
        title: 'Perform Tools Action from Jira Tickets',
        content: `
            <h3>Description</h3>
            <p>This feature lets technicians perform commonly used system management actions on a managed endpoint — such as shutdown, restart, wake-on-LAN, command prompt, registry editor, and task manager — directly from within <strong>Jira</strong> tickets.</p>

            <h3>How This Works</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Open a ticket in Jira that has an asset managed by Vulnerability Manager Plus.</li>
                <li>Click the <strong>"Tools"</strong> action button to see available system tools.</li>
                <li>Select the desired tool (e.g., Shutdown, Restart, Wake-on-LAN, Registry Editor, Command Prompt).</li>
                <li>The request is sent to Vulnerability Manager Plus via API, which executes the action via the agent on the target endpoint.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>The Vulnerability Manager Plus agent must be installed and online on the target endpoint.</li>
                <li>Integration between Vulnerability Manager Plus and Jira must be active.</li>
                <li>Technician must have the appropriate "Tools" permission in Vulnerability Manager Plus.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Known Limitations</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Some tools (e.g., Wake-on-LAN) require the endpoint's network adapter to support the feature.</li>
                <li>If the agent is offline, real-time tools like Command Prompt or Task Manager will fail.</li>
                <li>Shutdown/restart actions are irreversible — a confirmation prompt will appear before execution.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Logs for Troubleshooting</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Vulnerability Manager Plus server:</strong> <code>&lt;Install_Dir&gt;/logs/tools.log</code></li>
                <li><strong>Agent side:</strong> <code>&lt;Agent_Dir&gt;/logs/dcagentservicelog.txt</code></li>
                <li>Verify agent online status in Vulnerability Manager Plus → Scope of Management.</li>
            </ul>
            
        `,
        links: []
    },
